---
version: 1
op: attend.compress
description: compress a tool-result payload to a salience budget, preserving content relevant to intent
max_output_tokens: 600
vars: [raw, intent, max_tokens]
---
Compress the source below to AT MOST {{.max_tokens}} tokens, preserving content directly relevant to:

Intent: {{.intent}}

Source:
```
{{.raw}}
```

Rules:
- Preserve concrete facts the intent depends on: identifiers (function/class/file names), numbers, paths, error messages, decision-bearing sentences. Drop boilerplate, license headers, blank lines, navigation prose.
- Compress aggressively. Bullet points and abbreviated phrases beat full sentences. If a section is irrelevant to the intent, omit it entirely — do not summarize it.
- Do NOT invent facts. If the source does not mention something the intent asks about, say so plainly ("(no X found)") rather than guessing.
- Output the compressed content as plain text. No prose framing, no markdown fences, no "Here is the compressed version:" preamble. Start with the first piece of useful content.
